.TH ABRAFLEXI-MATCHER-IN 1 "July 17, 2026" "abraflexi-matcher" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
abraflexi-matcher-in \- Match all capable received invoices against outgoing payments in AbraFlexi
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B abraflexi-matcher-in
[OPTIONS]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B abraflexi-matcher-in
matches unpaid received invoices (bills owed to suppliers) against
outgoing bank payments recorded in AbraFlexi, over the last
.B MATCHER_DAYS_BACK
days.
.SH OPTIONS
This script uses environment variables for configuration.
.TP
.B RESULT_FILE
Path to the output JSON report file.
.TP
.B MATCHER_DAYS_BACK
Number of days to look back for payments (default: 365)
.TP
.B MATCHER_LOCALIZE
Locale for log/report messages: en_US (default), cs_CZ, or sk_SK.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The script requires AbraFlexi connection details:
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_URL
AbraFlexi server URL
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_LOGIN
AbraFlexi login username
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_PASSWORD
AbraFlexi password
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_COMPANY
AbraFlexi company code
.SH FILES
.TP
.I match_report.json
Default output file containing the matching results in JSON format compliant with the multiflexi report schema.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR abraflexi-matcher (1),
.BR abraflexi-matcher-out (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Vitex Software.
